            AID[+goods][+needed][+gift][+money/+food/+medicine] 
            Note: refers to tangible goods or supplies, e.g., money, medicine, food
        </commentary>
        <examples>Foreign aid to that region increased by twenty million dollars this year. The U.N. is threatening to cut off financial aid to that nation but not medical aid. The aid to the refugee camps came in the form of blankets, clean water and food. Three aids workers were kidnapped.</examples>
